en_219511_0	The Joint opposition accuses that the SOFA agreement permits the US army to act without any hindrance in Sri Lanka.
en_219511_1	Parliamentarian Bandula Gunawardena expressed this view at a media briefing convened by its Economic Research unit in Colombo this morning.
en_219511_2	However, The U.S. envoy in Colombo has said The United States has no plan or intention to establish a US base in Sri Lanka.
en_219511_3	US Ambassador to Sri Lanka Alaina B. Teplitz in a Twitter post dismissed recent reports published in media on the draft of the Status of Forces Agreement as "blatant misinformation".
en_219511_4	Teplitz said Visiting Forces Agreement negotiations only aim to facilitate cooperation and any agreement will fully respect the sovereignty of Sri Lanka.
